1. create a html form (form.html)
2.create a node js file (index.js)
	(a) require express,fs,ejs,path,body-parser
	 b) using app.use(express.json());  // recognize the incoming Request object as a JSON object
	(c) conect connetion file and schema file
	(d) using app.get method and add form .html file
	(e) using app.post method get all data from form and save on mongo{
		-insert our req.body data in datainfo variable
		-save data through await datainfo.save();		
	}	
	(f) using get and view all mongo data on our web page using ejs file{
		res.render('ejs filename','send data on ejs file') ->send data on ejs file 
}
	(g) app.listen ->start server on port 

3.conn.js file in all connection code with mongodb
4. schema.js file in set schema of json and create a collection and export collection
